text: Papyrus Oxyrhynchus 656 (abbreviated as P.Oxy.IV 656, VH 13, LBAD 3094, or Rahlfs 905) â€“ is a Greek fragment of a Septuagint manuscript written on papyrus in codex form. This manuscript was discovered at Oxyrhynchus, and it has been catalogued with number 656 according the list of septuagint manuscripts of Alfred Rahlfs. By comparative writing styles (palaeography), it has been dated to 3rd-century. == Sources == * * * * Category:3rd-century biblical manuscripts Category:Septuagint manuscripts
